Articles.Content: Once I can find a functioning guide for RF, I'll make a RF configs for F9.

Okay, so I've updated the Strongbacks to fit nicely with Kart's Falcons. I also added a ModuleManager config to add an attachment node to the Octaweb.

Link to the strongbacks: https://www.dropbox.com/sh/v1aqe9p0jd00nmp/AADYD8QEEgH-6-x8hBLsidHEa?dl=0

Can I just say splendid job on the detail!

Im using your Atlas V in RSS/RO - Looking great! 

Cant wait to use your Falcons!
Hey, not sure if anyone else caught this. F9 1.1 and 1.1-FT only have three second stage attachment points on the interstage, not 4 as in in the current model.

Just now, saabstory88 said:

Hey, not sure if anyone else caught this. F9 1.1 and 1.1-FT only have three second stage attachment points on the interstage, not 4 as in in the current model.

I've looked at some high rez pics of the new F 1.1FT on the pad, and it appears to only have 3 attach points, same as the original F9 1.1
What I meant by current model is Kart's current KSP model. Falcon 9 1.0 had 12, Falcon 9 1.1 and 1.1-FT have three. Kart has 4 in his KSP model.

10 minutes ago, saabstory88 said:

What I meant by current model is Kart's current KSP model. Falcon 9 1.0 had 12, Falcon 9 1.1 and 1.1-FT have three. Kart has 4 in his KSP model.

Yes I know. When I made Falcon 9 1.1 FT, there were no images of it available. I've used spaceflight101.com as my main source for the FT, there it said that there were 4 attachment points. I will change this, along with some other changes. And generally, there's a bigger difference between F9 1.1 and 1.1 FT from the outside than I expected. I'll adjust F9 1.1 FT once more images will be relased.

Edited December 20, 2015 by Kartoffelkuchen

Great! Also, there is a GSE interface on both sides of the Octoweb. They are on directly opposite sides. 

 

Edited December 20, 2015 by saabstory88
Alright thanks @saabstory88!
Wow! I forgot about this mod! This mod really came far!

5 minutes ago, Kartoffelkuchen said:

Alright thanks @saabstory88!

No, thank you! I love this pack!

I am curious about the gridfins. I know this is only the F9R but here you can see that the gridfins not only pivot up/out but rotate for roll control. Yours work great, just a small nitpick. From what I've experienced, control surfaces can be difficult so I can't really complain.

Also, I would definitely wait until better pictures are released of multiple F9FTs. A thought that came to mind when I saw people discussing why they haven't started using black landing legs, maybe they are using some older hardware from the non-FT models. I'm pretty sure there were still a couple of non-FT boosters that were set to fly before the the CRS-7 accident, including the JASON booster out in Vandenburg. I'll read up a little more on it though.

Edited December 21, 2015 by ReventonHawx

@ReventonHawx Yes, the grid fins in real life are working a bit different than these here. First of, they deploy and then individually pivot up or down, where we can only deploy them (-> Airbrake) or leave all undeployed and then pivot them out. 

And yes, they also provide roll control. Though unfortunately, this can't be done in KSP right now, so I had to add simply a roll torque for it.

Yes, I'll be waiting with F9 FT upgrades for my rocket a little while. 

I don't think that they are using any 1.1 hardware anymore on F9 FT. I believe they've made some changes to the landing legs, and tgey would definetely fly these on this mission, since it's their first RTLS attempt. I bet the landing legs will stay white, since the falcon on spacex.com is inly an artistic impression. The f9 1.1 was also shown with a black interstage there, so I wouldn't really trust the site renders. It's just a visualization.
